commentTextItems.html: and that's that- pulled behind square to complete an easy victory for Ireland

commentPostTextItems.html: Thanks for joining us from Dublin, we're back tomorrow at the same time for Scotland against The Netherlands. Ireland march on after a comprehensive victory but the Dutch must improve in all areas if they are to test Scotland tomorrow.
Please join me tomorrow for a 10.45am start in Clontarf, Dublin. Cheers.

milestones.description: Andre Botha and Niall O'Brien's 89-run partnership is IRE's highest for the 3rd wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 80 between Niall O'Brien and Eoin Morgan
Andre Botha has become the top wicket-taker for IRE in ODIs with 27 wickets, going past Dave Langford-Smith's 25
Porterfield has broken the record for most catches (12) in ODIs for IRE, going past Johnston's 11
This is the lowest match aggregate (285) involving teams Netherlands & Ireland in ODIs
